WEBVTT

00:02.045 --> 00:03.394
[bombs exploding,
machine-gun fire]

00:03.873 --> 00:05.788
[man] Fire! Fire!

00:05.831 --> 00:08.008
[Jackson screaming]

00:09.574 --> 00:11.054
Jackson!

00:12.055 --> 00:14.231
[Jackson groaning]

00:16.059 --> 00:17.495
[sobbing]

00:17.539 --> 00:19.323
Hey, you're gonna be
safe down here.

00:19.367 --> 00:21.325
Jackson, I got you.
Hey, look at me.

00:21.369 --> 00:23.327
Look at me.
You're gonna be okay.

00:23.371 --> 00:24.067
Sarge...

00:24.111 --> 00:25.416
Sergeant,

00:25.460 --> 00:26.939
I can't feel my legs,
are they there?

00:26.983 --> 00:28.028
I can't look.

00:30.813 --> 00:32.423
Sarge, are they there?

00:33.990 --> 00:35.209
Are they?

00:40.257 --> 00:42.477
[glass shattering]

00:44.740 --> 00:46.176
[knocking]

00:46.220 --> 00:48.222
[Jackson] Contact.
Two o'clock, 150 meters.

00:48.265 --> 00:50.180
Contact. Two o'clock
130 meters.

00:50.224 --> 00:51.138
Eric, Stand down.

00:51.181 --> 00:52.226
[Eric grunts]

00:55.403 --> 00:59.059
Eric, it's me, Eric.
Don't shoot

00:59.102 --> 01:00.756
[grunting]

01:02.453 --> 01:06.588
Okay. Okay. Shh...
You're okay. You're okay.

01:13.116 --> 01:15.336
Nighthawk, can you hear me?

01:15.379 --> 01:17.338
[Betty on radio]
Loud and clear, Base station.

01:17.381 --> 01:20.123
I'm still a bumper sticker
on this shady-ass truck,

01:20.167 --> 01:21.646
headed north.

01:21.690 --> 01:24.649
He's approaching the westbound
turn off at Exit 49.

01:27.783 --> 01:30.090
That's too far. Two more miles
and you'll be out of range.

01:30.133 --> 01:31.526
Hold on. He's pulling over.

01:33.441 --> 01:35.399
I'm going to park
and approach him on foot.

01:35.443 --> 01:40.622
Betty, just please,
please be careful.

01:46.062 --> 01:47.150
[Betty] Hey.

01:49.848 --> 01:51.633
[trucker] Didn't think
I'd come across anyone.

01:51.676 --> 01:54.853
Yeah, I'm just taking a break,
stretching my legs.

01:54.897 --> 01:58.683
It gets lonely out here
on the long, dark road.

01:58.727 --> 02:02.034
You want some company,
even for a little bit?

02:02.078 --> 02:03.384
What, in the woods?

02:04.211 --> 02:05.864
Or maybe back in my truck?

02:05.908 --> 02:07.214
That sounds good.

02:07.257 --> 02:08.824
[suspenseful music plays]

02:12.523 --> 02:14.699
Do you do this a lot?

02:14.743 --> 02:16.919
Pick up pretty girls
on the side of the road?

02:16.962 --> 02:18.355
[Betty chuckles]

02:18.399 --> 02:21.793
I guess I've had my fair
share of encounters, yeah.

02:23.143 --> 02:27.277
Uh, before we do this, uh...

02:27.321 --> 02:29.105
I just wanna make sure
that you've got cash.

02:29.149 --> 02:31.194
That's all I needed to hear.

02:31.238 --> 02:32.717
[banging]

02:32.761 --> 02:34.284
-FBI, freeze!
-Don't move.

02:34.328 --> 02:35.633
What is this?

02:35.677 --> 02:38.027
FBI. We're taking you in
for solicitation.

02:38.070 --> 02:39.289
Okay, This is a mistake.

02:39.333 --> 02:41.465
I am also with the FBI.

02:41.509 --> 02:45.600
No, you're not, Betty.
You quit, remember?

02:48.385 --> 02:49.995
What the hell are you
doing out here?

02:50.039 --> 02:52.215
I'm trying to catch our killer.
What are you doing, Glen?

02:52.259 --> 02:54.174
I'm trying to clean up
the Lonely Highway.

02:54.217 --> 02:55.958
By entrapping young women?

02:56.001 --> 02:58.656
We should be helping them,
not arresting them.

02:58.700 --> 03:01.268
God, I should have stabbed you
harder when I had the chance.

03:01.311 --> 03:05.663
You do realize
it's illegal to impersonate
an FBI agent, right?

03:05.707 --> 03:07.752
You shouldn't have
that badge or a gun.

03:08.492 --> 03:10.233
Hand them over.

03:10.277 --> 03:11.365
Or should I arrest you?

03:12.366 --> 03:14.324
[soft music playing]

03:28.338 --> 03:30.558
[eerie music plays]

03:35.911 --> 03:37.565
Wait. Kevin?

03:41.830 --> 03:44.615
Compulsion, thy name is
Kevin of Finland.

03:47.575 --> 03:49.751
Does Eric have
chronic nightmares
that you know of?

03:49.794 --> 03:54.408
Yeah, but I mean
nothing like last night.

03:54.451 --> 03:55.757
Looks like he was living it.

03:57.411 --> 04:00.414
What about you?
Any nightmares since the war?

04:02.111 --> 04:04.896
Um, yeah, at first...

04:04.940 --> 04:06.550
but I haven't had one
in months.

04:09.466 --> 04:11.251
I've known
soldiers like Eric.

04:11.294 --> 04:12.600
They've crossed a Rubicon,

04:12.643 --> 04:14.515
the only way back is with
professional help.

04:14.558 --> 04:17.387
Well, wasn't there a recovery
place that Eric was supposed
to go to?

04:17.431 --> 04:19.781
Yeah, he tried calling a
bunch of times

04:19.824 --> 04:23.654
and they kept promising
him a spot, but still nothing.

04:24.351 --> 04:26.266
Well, don't give up.

04:26.309 --> 04:28.485
In the meantime, I'm going
to look into something else.

04:33.490 --> 04:35.492
What are those?

04:35.536 --> 04:38.365
Leads I got on the DL from
from one of my former
colleagues in New York.

04:38.408 --> 04:42.282
Names of fat cats with money
burning holes in their pockets.

04:42.325 --> 04:43.457
Potential investors.

04:43.500 --> 04:44.936
Branching out from jewelry?

04:44.980 --> 04:47.287
I need to start
making money, Reggie.

04:47.330 --> 04:51.769
Real money to replace
all the funds that Chad lost
in his pathetic Ponzi scheme.

04:51.813 --> 04:54.119
Funds, I'm responsible
for, the snake.

04:54.163 --> 04:57.732
So I'm getting back into
aggressive investment banking.

04:57.775 --> 05:00.256
Don't you have to be
on Wall Street to do that?

05:00.300 --> 05:01.649
A common misconception.

05:01.692 --> 05:06.131
All you need is two things.
This and names.

05:06.175 --> 05:08.699
Which means time
to make it rain.

05:10.658 --> 05:12.224
Good morning, Cheryl.

05:12.268 --> 05:13.487
Can I help you?

05:14.575 --> 05:16.403
No, no, no. Sweet Kevin.

05:16.446 --> 05:19.449
The question is,
can I help you?

05:19.493 --> 05:20.972
We saw each other in the woods.

05:21.016 --> 05:23.279
I was seeking inspiration
for my next sermon.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.412
But what about you?

05:25.455 --> 05:29.503
I thought you gave up cruising
after your latest violent
encounter in the steam room.

05:29.546 --> 05:31.548
I did, for a while.

05:31.592 --> 05:34.899
I see. Do you know
what I believe, Kevin?

05:34.943 --> 05:36.988
I don't think you were
just looking for a hook-up.

05:37.032 --> 05:39.774
I also think you were
looking for meaning.

05:40.427 --> 05:41.950
Peace.

05:41.993 --> 05:45.432
No, I'm pretty sure I was just
looking for a hook-up.

05:47.172 --> 05:49.261
Kev-Kev...

05:49.305 --> 05:53.614
I don't know if you've heard,
but my mother and I recently
started a ministry.

05:53.657 --> 05:55.659
Why don't you
come to a service?

05:55.703 --> 05:57.574
You might find the answers
you're looking for.

05:57.618 --> 06:01.622
No offense, Cheryl,
but that sounds like a
classic Blossom scam.

06:01.665 --> 06:04.451
Well, I can't speak
for Mumsy, but...

06:05.234 --> 06:06.757
for me, it's no scam.

06:06.801 --> 06:10.935
Understand my calling is
for a higher purpose.

06:10.979 --> 06:16.201
Since I began ministering,
I felt the best I have since...

06:16.245 --> 06:18.900
well, since the night
of that misbegotten key party.

06:20.728 --> 06:23.687
What's the harm in trying
one service?

06:23.731 --> 06:26.560
Okay, yeah. I'll come
just to check it out.

06:29.911 --> 06:32.740
You're lucky it was Glen
and not the Highway Killer.

06:32.783 --> 06:34.219
You would have been
on your own.

06:34.263 --> 06:36.526
Well, I didn't want to
lose him.

06:36.570 --> 06:39.399
Anyways. I doubt I'll be
spending much more time
on the lonely highway

06:39.442 --> 06:41.575
now that Glen's gunning for me.

06:42.750 --> 06:47.363
So maybe we bring the
Lonely Highway here...

06:47.407 --> 06:49.539
to Pop's, and the Whyte Wyrm.

06:50.192 --> 06:51.585
Go on.

06:51.628 --> 06:54.501
The Highway Killer is most
likely a trucker, right?

06:54.544 --> 06:58.983
-Mm.
-Well, what if we offer
something to lure truckers in?

06:59.027 --> 07:00.071
Entertainment?

07:00.898 --> 07:02.073
Smart.

07:02.117 --> 07:03.988
We're not going after
"truckers" plural,

07:04.032 --> 07:06.034
we're going after
one trucker in particular,

07:06.077 --> 07:09.559
or killer, who is targeting...
young women.

07:11.039 --> 07:14.259
Okay, crazy idea.
Have you ever seen Coyote Ugly?

07:14.303 --> 07:17.611
Um, please.
Can't Fight The Moonlight
is one of my karaoke go-to's.

07:17.654 --> 07:21.528
Okay, so maybe that's what
we need to tempt
our little friend.

07:21.571 --> 07:24.095
Riverdale's very own
Coyote Ugly.

07:24.139 --> 07:28.099
And we can wire Pop's
and the Wyrm
with close circuit cameras,

07:28.143 --> 07:31.842
and we could start compiling
a database that not even
the FBI has.

07:31.886 --> 07:34.105
Tracking regulars,
running license plates.

07:34.149 --> 07:36.630
Let's do it. Together.

07:37.674 --> 07:38.806
We'll talk to Fangs.

07:41.635 --> 07:42.984
Six hours.

07:43.027 --> 07:44.725
We wait six hours to see
someone and they tell us

07:44.768 --> 07:47.292
we haven't filled out
the right forms.

07:47.336 --> 07:51.035
Sorry, Sarge, but that's what
happens every time I go
down to the VA.

07:51.079 --> 07:53.168
[Frank] Archie, Eric, Come into
the living room.

07:57.825 --> 08:00.480
Fellas, meet our new roommate.

08:00.523 --> 08:02.612
[dog panting]

08:04.701 --> 08:06.050
[gentle instrumental plays]

08:12.753 --> 08:14.319
Where did you get this idea
from, Uncle Frank?

08:14.363 --> 08:15.930
I've known a lot of veterans
who adopted pets.

08:15.973 --> 08:18.062
It's a part of their transition
back to civilian life.

08:18.106 --> 08:19.455
Helps with their anxiety,

08:19.499 --> 08:20.500
adds structure to their day,

08:20.543 --> 08:22.197
gives them a loyal companion.

08:22.240 --> 08:23.503
Where'd you get him?

08:23.546 --> 08:25.330
Got him out of
the shelter downtown.

08:25.374 --> 08:27.507
According to the vet,
they found him near a dumpster.

08:27.550 --> 08:29.683
[Eric] They tell you
what happened to his ears?

08:29.726 --> 08:31.728
No, they weren't sure.

08:31.772 --> 08:34.731
Hey, Arch, didn't you have
a dog last time I was here?
what was his name?

08:34.775 --> 08:35.645
Vegas.

08:35.689 --> 08:37.212
What happened to him?

08:37.255 --> 08:39.388
When I enlisted, Mom took him
to Chicago with her.

08:40.258 --> 08:41.695
He died while I was overseas.

08:42.478 --> 08:43.479
Aah, damn.

08:44.959 --> 08:46.221
I'm sorry, Arch.

08:46.874 --> 08:48.571
He was my best friend.

08:48.615 --> 08:51.705
Well, maybe this little pooch
will be good for both of you.

08:59.408 --> 09:05.675
♪ Blessed be
The tie that binds ♪

09:05.719 --> 09:12.029
♪ Our hearts
In Christian love ♪

09:12.073 --> 09:14.989
♪ The fellowship...

09:15.032 --> 09:16.294
[Veronica] Well,
let me ask you this.

09:16.338 --> 09:18.122
Have you ever invested
in an IPO before?

09:18.166 --> 09:20.734
Because we have
numerous opportunities
in the pipeline

09:20.777 --> 09:22.692
that I'd be happy
to walk you through.

09:25.347 --> 09:26.827
Of course, Mr. Mamet.

09:26.870 --> 09:28.698
Thank you for your time.

09:28.742 --> 09:30.091
[disconnects call]

09:30.961 --> 09:32.572
You win some, you lose some.

09:32.615 --> 09:35.575
Yes, but I'm losing
more than I'm winning, Reggie.

09:35.618 --> 09:38.316
Back in New York,
when I was the She-Wolf
of Wall Street,

09:38.360 --> 09:39.883
I had a team of 20
working under me.

09:39.927 --> 09:44.888
But now, I'm one broker
with no firm to back her up.

09:44.932 --> 09:46.934
Then let's double our chances.

09:46.977 --> 09:48.239
Let me work for you.

09:48.283 --> 09:49.719
Reggie, you can't
just start trading.

09:49.763 --> 09:52.287
You have to understand
finance, politics...

09:52.330 --> 09:54.071
-diplomacy.
-Really?

09:54.115 --> 09:56.900
Because I've been
listening to you all day,

09:56.944 --> 09:58.293
and it sounds to me like

09:58.336 --> 09:59.773
you just need to know
how to close a sale,

09:59.816 --> 10:02.079
like I do at my old man's
used car lot.

10:02.123 --> 10:04.125
I can close, Ronnie.

10:04.865 --> 10:06.301
I'm a closer.

10:06.344 --> 10:07.868
Give me a shot.

10:07.911 --> 10:08.782
Okay.

10:11.480 --> 10:12.873
It's two o'clock now.

10:13.700 --> 10:14.570
If you can turn

10:14.614 --> 10:15.832
one of these leads into a sale

10:15.876 --> 10:17.878
by the time
the Stock Exchange closes,

10:18.922 --> 10:19.880
I'll cut you in.

10:19.923 --> 10:20.837
One client?

10:20.881 --> 10:21.969
By six o'clock?

10:22.012 --> 10:23.144
The New York Stock exchange

10:23.187 --> 10:24.711
closes at 4:00 ,Reggie.

10:26.713 --> 10:27.627
Clock's ticking.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.632
[Betty] So, Fangs,
we have an idea

10:32.675 --> 10:34.851
that we would love for you
to run by Toni.

10:34.895 --> 10:36.287
Okay.

10:36.331 --> 10:37.985
If we want to attract
the Highway Killer,

10:38.028 --> 10:40.727
we have to give him
something enticing to look at.

10:40.770 --> 10:43.120
So what do you think about
turning this place into

10:43.164 --> 10:46.297
a full-blown
Coyote Ugly-style bar?

10:46.341 --> 10:47.908
Like the Tyra Banks movie?

10:47.951 --> 10:49.257
-Hm-mm.
-Exactly.

10:49.300 --> 10:50.780
Hot ladies dancing on the bar,

10:50.824 --> 10:52.521
fully clothed, of course,

10:52.564 --> 10:54.697
-[Fangs sighs]
-and free-flowing booze.

10:54.741 --> 10:56.656
It would be
the perfect thirst trap.

11:01.443 --> 11:02.879
And who are the hot ladies?

11:03.706 --> 11:04.576
[Tabitha] Us.

11:05.055 --> 11:06.361
We are.

11:08.145 --> 11:09.146
Yes, I'm just trying

11:09.190 --> 11:10.670
to get a referral to a doctor.

11:13.107 --> 11:14.325
Again, my name is

11:14.369 --> 11:15.413
Sergeant Archie Andrews,

11:15.457 --> 11:16.327
I'm calling on behalf of

11:16.371 --> 11:17.546
Corporal Eric Jackson

11:17.589 --> 11:18.678
about getting him
some treatment.

11:20.201 --> 11:21.724
I've left my number
with you before,

11:21.768 --> 11:22.899
If you could give me
a call back,

11:22.943 --> 11:23.857
that would be great.

11:25.075 --> 11:25.946
Thank you.

11:29.384 --> 11:31.212
[sighs in exasperation]

11:32.082 --> 11:33.431
[Frank] How are you doing?

11:35.825 --> 11:36.957
Thinking about Vegas?

11:38.045 --> 11:39.220
No.

11:39.263 --> 11:41.004
I'm thinking about Bingo.

11:41.048 --> 11:42.266
Who's Bingo?

11:44.704 --> 11:45.617
Uh...

11:46.488 --> 11:48.795
He was this stray dog...

11:48.838 --> 11:50.405
that our platoon adopted.

11:52.015 --> 11:52.973
What happened to him?

11:53.843 --> 11:54.714
He didn't make it..

11:55.627 --> 11:56.759
Yeah.

11:56.803 --> 11:58.152
We don't like
talking about him much.

11:58.195 --> 11:59.544
It's probably why
Eric gets so happy

11:59.588 --> 12:00.937
about getting this new dog...

12:02.417 --> 12:03.897
to make up for Bingo.

12:04.898 --> 12:05.986
Yeah,

12:06.029 --> 12:07.248
that makes sense.

12:11.078 --> 12:12.296
[clock ticking]

12:12.340 --> 12:14.037
[Reggie] I want this for you,

12:14.081 --> 12:16.953
and more importantly,
you should want this
for yourself.

12:16.997 --> 12:19.042
You're a smart guy, Bobby,

12:19.086 --> 12:22.698
I mean, just think about
what this type of investment
could mean for your family.

12:22.742 --> 12:25.222
I'm talking
a down payment
on the house,

12:25.266 --> 12:28.356
college tuition
for your son or daughter,

12:28.399 --> 12:30.097
vacations you deserve

12:30.140 --> 12:32.273
but haven't been
able to afford.

12:32.316 --> 12:34.057
[inhales] You're in
at a hundred?

12:34.101 --> 12:36.320
[upbeat music plays]

12:37.278 --> 12:38.932
[breathes] Mr. Stone,

12:38.975 --> 12:41.891
I'm telling you,
you won't regret this.

12:41.935 --> 12:42.979
Hmm-mm.

12:43.023 --> 12:44.589
I'll email you the paperwork.

12:45.112 --> 12:45.939
Hm-mm.

12:47.854 --> 12:50.204
Very good, Reginald,

12:50.247 --> 12:51.988
you're a natural salesman.

12:52.032 --> 12:55.818
Welcome, officially,
to Pearls and Posh.

12:55.862 --> 12:58.255
Look, Cheryl, I don't mean
to offend you or anything,

12:58.299 --> 13:01.302
but your service
wasn't exactly my speed.

13:01.868 --> 13:03.434
To each his own.

13:03.478 --> 13:05.436
But there is a hole inside you

13:05.480 --> 13:07.134
that you're trying
to fill, Kevin,

13:07.177 --> 13:09.005
and I think I know
what it's about.

13:09.876 --> 13:11.138
Fangs...

13:11.181 --> 13:12.443
how you left things with him.

13:14.968 --> 13:16.447
[inhales]

13:16.491 --> 13:17.797
Breaking up with him...

13:18.623 --> 13:20.147
especially the way I did,

13:20.190 --> 13:22.845
is the worst thing I've done,

13:22.889 --> 13:23.933
maybe ever.

13:23.977 --> 13:24.804
Regret...

13:25.543 --> 13:26.762
it haunts you.

13:27.894 --> 13:30.679
I know because
it haunts me, too.

13:32.420 --> 13:34.030
Go to your man,

13:34.074 --> 13:35.466
try to make amends,

13:35.510 --> 13:36.903
say you're sorry,

13:37.512 --> 13:38.905
ask for clemency.

13:39.819 --> 13:41.298
Regardless of how he responds,

13:41.342 --> 13:43.083
you'll feel better
having tried.

13:45.085 --> 13:46.521
[knock on door]

13:50.046 --> 13:51.569
Kevin!

13:51.613 --> 13:53.702
Hey, uh, this...
this is a surprise.

13:54.355 --> 13:55.486
Hey, Fangs.

13:56.923 --> 13:58.489
I know we haven't
talked for awhile,

13:58.533 --> 14:00.274
but I got some stuff
to get off my chest.

14:00.317 --> 14:01.666
so I hope you'll hear me out.

14:01.710 --> 14:02.972
For sure, of course,

14:03.016 --> 14:04.626
uh, just right now
isn't a good time.

14:04.669 --> 14:06.106
If I don't say it now,

14:06.149 --> 14:07.411
I'm gonna lose my nerves.

14:07.455 --> 14:09.500
-Just, just, just...
-[Fangs sighs]

14:09.936 --> 14:10.762
Kev...

14:10.806 --> 14:12.721
More baguette to the rescue.

14:14.201 --> 14:15.419
-Oh, my God.
-Kevin!

14:15.463 --> 14:16.594
Oh, my God. Moose?

14:16.638 --> 14:17.682
Hey, it's been a while, huh?

14:17.726 --> 14:19.032
[Fangs] Kev, this isn't...

14:19.075 --> 14:20.772
This isn't what it looks.

14:20.816 --> 14:22.470
You're seeing Moose Mason?

14:22.513 --> 14:24.211
We just...
we just ran into each other.

14:24.254 --> 14:26.691
Kev, why don't you sit down?

14:26.735 --> 14:29.172
Have a glass of wine,
we can talk about this.

14:29.216 --> 14:30.565
[Kevin] Yeah, no, thank you.

14:30.608 --> 14:32.872
I've got to wake up
from this nightmare

14:32.915 --> 14:35.700
in which
my ex-boyfriends
are sleeping together.

14:35.744 --> 14:37.877
[dramatic music plays]

14:38.399 --> 14:39.487
Kevin.

14:40.401 --> 14:42.011
[bombs exploding,
machine-gun fire]

14:42.969 --> 14:44.971
[Jackson groaning]

14:46.407 --> 14:48.278
Hey, Eric,

14:48.322 --> 14:49.540
I know you're tired,

14:49.584 --> 14:50.933
but you gotta wait
until nightfall,

14:50.977 --> 14:52.717
and then I could
carry you out of here.

14:52.761 --> 14:54.371
Hey, we're gonna get you help,

14:54.415 --> 14:55.720
but you gotta keep
your eyes open.

14:55.764 --> 14:58.288
[dog barks, bomb explodes]

14:58.332 --> 14:59.768
-[dog whines]
-[Eric groans]

14:59.811 --> 15:01.161
[Jackson] I'm sure this is...

15:01.988 --> 15:03.032
Is that Bingo?

15:03.076 --> 15:03.990
-[dog barks]
-Yeah.

15:04.033 --> 15:05.034
I'm gonna bring him back.

15:05.078 --> 15:06.340
Where is he?

15:06.383 --> 15:07.645
He's in the middle
of no-man's land.

15:07.689 --> 15:09.473
[mutters] That's no good.

15:09.517 --> 15:11.214
You can't go out there,
you'll get shot.

15:11.258 --> 15:12.563
I can make it if I'm fast.

15:12.607 --> 15:14.087
[bullets whizzing]

15:14.130 --> 15:16.393
You can't go out there,
Sarge, no way.

15:16.437 --> 15:18.178
I can't just ignore him, Eric.

15:18.221 --> 15:19.919
You'll die.

15:19.962 --> 15:22.138
You're my only hope
of getting out of
this foxhole alive.

15:22.182 --> 15:24.749
I can get Bingo
and I can bring him back,
and I can take you both.

15:24.793 --> 15:26.664
We're in their crosshairs.

15:26.708 --> 15:27.927
You've gotta wait them out.

15:27.970 --> 15:29.102
I have to do it,

15:29.145 --> 15:30.842
I can't just leave Bingo
out there to die.

15:30.886 --> 15:33.280
[Jackson] Sarge, no,
I won't let you.

15:33.323 --> 15:35.586
[groans and thuds]

15:35.630 --> 15:37.240
Eric, what the hell?

15:37.284 --> 15:39.547
-Sarge, you gotta help.
The dog, he's gone.
-What?

15:39.590 --> 15:41.636
He's missing,
we gotta find him.

15:45.292 --> 15:46.728
How did he get out?

15:46.771 --> 15:48.904
Hey, guys, it's okay,
calm down, I found him.

15:48.948 --> 15:49.644
Where?

15:49.687 --> 15:50.819
Come here, check it out.

15:53.256 --> 15:55.215
[soft music playing]

15:56.172 --> 15:57.086
[sighs]

15:58.000 --> 16:00.524
-[door creaks]
-[Archie exhales]

16:00.568 --> 16:01.961
[Archie]
How'd he get in there?

16:02.004 --> 16:04.137
I don't know,
I guess the door was ajar.

16:05.181 --> 16:06.617
He was looking
for a place to hide.

16:06.661 --> 16:08.097
[dog whines]

16:10.360 --> 16:12.972
[upbeat music playing]

16:13.015 --> 16:17.193
Mr. Preston,
it's Reginald Mantle
from Pearls and Posh.

16:17.237 --> 16:19.456
Boy, do I have
an exciting proposition
for you.

16:19.500 --> 16:22.720
[Veronica] Yes, Mr. Gibbs,
we're smaller than some of
the New York firms,

16:22.764 --> 16:25.462
but it means we'll work
that much harder for you.

16:25.506 --> 16:27.116
And just to be clear,

16:27.160 --> 16:30.554
though I want your business,
I don't need your business.

16:30.598 --> 16:32.904
[rock music playing]

16:32.948 --> 16:34.645
[Reggie] Look, Nolan,
there's no judgment here,

16:34.689 --> 16:36.821
if you wanna go
the target mutual funds route.

16:36.865 --> 16:38.214
I get it, it's safe.

16:38.258 --> 16:39.476
But the truth is,

16:39.520 --> 16:41.043
scared money
doesn't make money.

16:41.087 --> 16:43.480
What I'm offering you
is a sure thing.

16:43.524 --> 16:45.482
Welcome aboard, Mrs. Artemis,

16:45.526 --> 16:48.746
you will surely be bragging
to your friends at tea time
this Saturday,

16:48.790 --> 16:50.487
speak to you very, very soon.

16:50.531 --> 16:52.054
Okay, bye, bye.

16:53.360 --> 16:55.318
I just closed my fifth client.

16:55.362 --> 16:57.799
I just closed my third...
we're killing it, Ronnie.

16:57.842 --> 16:59.714
We're proving ourselves
to be capable,

16:59.757 --> 17:01.672
that's for sure. But...

17:01.716 --> 17:02.847
we need more leads to call.

17:02.891 --> 17:05.241
I'm all tapped out of names.

17:05.285 --> 17:08.027
Ronnie, what's my commission
for all the fish I'm catching?

17:08.070 --> 17:09.941
Industry standard,
five percent.

17:09.985 --> 17:11.421
If I get us some fresh leads,

17:11.465 --> 17:12.857
will you bump me
to fifteen percent?

17:12.901 --> 17:15.686
If you can really
bring in new business,

17:15.730 --> 17:17.036
ten percent.

17:17.079 --> 17:19.299
Okay then,
but there's one caveat...

17:20.822 --> 17:23.042
the leads are from SoDale.

17:23.085 --> 17:25.435
SoDale?
What are you talking about?

17:25.479 --> 17:27.176
The thing about SoDale is...

17:27.220 --> 17:28.395
it doesn't exist.

17:28.438 --> 17:30.527
It's a muddy field
with no construction.

17:30.571 --> 17:32.094
Your dad sold his investors

17:32.138 --> 17:34.618
on a vision of something
that will never be built.

17:34.662 --> 17:37.534
He's using the money
to fund his crazy search
for palladium.

17:37.578 --> 17:40.233
What about his investors?
Aren't they asking questions?

17:40.276 --> 17:42.148
Constantly.

17:42.191 --> 17:44.628
But he's always got an excuse
for why the new houses
aren't finished.

17:44.672 --> 17:46.065
So, I'm thinking...

17:46.108 --> 17:49.546
What if we go after
my father's investors?

17:49.590 --> 17:52.201
And get them
to pull out of SoDale

17:52.245 --> 17:53.637
and invest with us?

17:54.638 --> 17:56.727
Reggie... you're a genius.

17:59.078 --> 18:00.209
[chuckles]

18:00.253 --> 18:02.255
[dog barking aggressively]

18:04.431 --> 18:07.042
[Frank] Hey, it's okay,
just calm down.
Put some pressure.

18:07.086 --> 18:08.696
Uncle Frank, Eric,
what the hell happened?

18:08.739 --> 18:10.567
Eric took the dog for a walk.
They ran into a bigger dog,

18:10.611 --> 18:12.700
Our guy freaked out,
Eric tried to calm him down...

18:12.743 --> 18:13.962
And he bit my arm...

18:14.005 --> 18:15.224
Okay, okay,
that's it, we're done.

18:15.268 --> 18:16.269
Where are you going?

18:16.312 --> 18:17.618
I'm calling the shelter.

18:17.661 --> 18:19.098
Arch, please,
this is all my fault...

18:19.141 --> 18:20.751
Just give me five minutes
to clean up Eric,

18:20.795 --> 18:22.144
and I'll explain everything.

18:22.188 --> 18:24.407
[dog barks]

18:24.451 --> 18:27.584
Okay, so how is a rescue dog
biting Eric your fault?

18:27.628 --> 18:30.457
The dog that I brought home
isn't an ordinary rescue,
Archie.

18:30.500 --> 18:33.155
The woman
at the shelter told me,
based on his injuries,

18:33.199 --> 18:36.115
he was very likely
part of a dog-fighting ring.

18:36.680 --> 18:38.204
Are you kidding?

18:38.247 --> 18:40.075
That's happening here
in Riverdale?

18:40.119 --> 18:41.642
Apparently,
they started popping up
a few years ago,

18:41.685 --> 18:42.947
after everyone
began moving away,

18:42.991 --> 18:44.819
leaving their pets behind.

18:44.862 --> 18:47.778
The shelter rescues
as many as they can but...

18:47.822 --> 18:49.258
some dogs just wind up
with the wrong people.

18:49.302 --> 18:51.521
Yeah, scumbags who pit dogs
against each other,

18:51.565 --> 18:54.655
and then bet on
which ones will win
and which ones will die.

18:54.698 --> 18:55.873
I'll be back.

18:56.570 --> 18:58.789
[dramatic music plays]

19:00.095 --> 19:02.445
Mrs. Rawald, you wouldn't
have happened to invest

19:02.489 --> 19:04.708
in SoDale LLC, by any chance?

19:04.752 --> 19:09.017
Uh-huh, and how is
that investment doing,
Mr. Barry?

19:09.060 --> 19:10.975
Have you seen any houses
in SoDale?

19:11.019 --> 19:12.847
Have you seen any blueprints?

19:12.890 --> 19:14.414
I'll be honest,

19:14.457 --> 19:16.459
construction's not happening
as quickly as I'd like.

19:16.503 --> 19:19.506
Mr. Barry, I have it
on very good authority

19:19.549 --> 19:21.595
that there will never be
a SoDale.

19:21.638 --> 19:23.292
So...

19:23.336 --> 19:27.209
might I suggest
you withdraw your funds
from SoDale LLC,

19:27.253 --> 19:29.820
and invest with us
here at Pearls and Posh?

19:29.864 --> 19:31.953
You're telling me
SoDale's a scam?

19:32.736 --> 19:34.173
Can you give me a minute,

19:34.216 --> 19:35.522
I'm just getting Hiram lodge
on the other line.

19:35.565 --> 19:36.871
Chris Barry,

19:36.914 --> 19:38.655
always a pleasure
to hear your voice...

19:38.699 --> 19:39.830
how's Cindy?

19:39.874 --> 19:41.789
I'm not happy.

19:41.832 --> 19:44.139
I have a source telling me
that I made a bad investment
with you...

19:44.183 --> 19:46.228
-[Chris] SoDale.
-Whoa!

19:46.272 --> 19:47.882
That's absurd.

19:47.925 --> 19:50.189
SoDale is the finest investment
you can put your money into.

19:50.232 --> 19:52.495
In fact,
you should double-down.

19:52.539 --> 19:55.237
How does thirty percent returns
over three years sound?

19:55.281 --> 19:57.021
He's selling me
on thirty percent

19:57.065 --> 19:58.632
at three years, Ms. Posh.

19:58.675 --> 19:59.937
Can you match that?

19:59.981 --> 20:04.333
How about
an ROY of 35% at three.

20:04.377 --> 20:07.031
And I'll throw in
a glamourge egg
as a closing bonus.

20:07.075 --> 20:08.119
But that's my final offer.

20:08.163 --> 20:09.947
What do you say, Chris?

20:09.991 --> 20:13.212
This is a onetime only
exclusive FOH,
Friends of Hiram offer.

20:13.255 --> 20:17.216
Thirty-five percent
and a glamourge egg.
Okay, I'm in.

20:18.521 --> 20:21.089
Thank you, Mr. Barry.

20:21.132 --> 20:24.223
You are in good hands
here at Pearls and Posh.

20:24.266 --> 20:29.532
Sorry Lodge, but I'm pulling
out of SoDale, and if I don't
get all my money back,

20:29.576 --> 20:31.404
I'll be calling
the state attorney's office.

20:31.447 --> 20:33.014
Best of luck with your venture.

20:37.279 --> 20:38.237
To you, Ronnie.

20:41.762 --> 20:43.372
The she-wolf of Wall Street.

20:44.460 --> 20:45.331
[glasses clink]

20:49.944 --> 20:52.425
So, what happens now?

20:52.468 --> 20:55.950
We take the night off
to help Betty and Tabitha,

20:55.993 --> 21:00.041
and then we keep doing
exactly what we're doing.

21:03.349 --> 21:05.264
[Cheryl] Fangs with Moose,
you say?

21:06.439 --> 21:09.093
Yeah, I caught them having
wine and cheese.

21:09.137 --> 21:11.574
Ew, that's diabolical.

21:11.618 --> 21:13.533
Kevin, you did nothing wrong.

21:13.576 --> 21:17.450
And you brought
your sacred truth
to his profane threshold.

21:17.493 --> 21:19.234
That alone is a victory.

21:19.278 --> 21:21.932
Then why do I feel so forsaken?

21:22.672 --> 21:23.543
Mm.

21:25.588 --> 21:30.289
In godless times like these,
instead of focusing
on yourself,

21:30.332 --> 21:34.467
perhaps the only way
to know true comfort
is by comforting others.

21:35.511 --> 21:37.774
Tonight, I'm assisting
Betty and Tabitha

21:37.818 --> 21:43.345
in the most ingenious ruse
to thwart the evil goings-on
of the Lonely Highway.

21:43.389 --> 21:48.394
Work with us on this, Kevin,
and perhaps in service,

21:48.437 --> 21:51.527
you will find peace
and meaning.

21:53.181 --> 21:55.966
[Betty] Okay, gather round,
people. This is it.

21:56.010 --> 21:57.794
Hopefully, it will be
a big night.

21:57.838 --> 22:01.972
We'll be checking
everyone's IDs,
aka, writing down their names,

22:02.016 --> 22:03.844
and driver's license numbers
regardless of their age.

22:03.887 --> 22:07.282
That's after my new cameras
catch their faces coming in.

22:07.326 --> 22:11.591
Mom, you'll be working the bar,
keeping an eye out for anything
and everything sketchy.

22:11.634 --> 22:12.896
As I usually do.

22:13.984 --> 22:15.290
Hey, shouldn't Fangs be here?

22:15.334 --> 22:17.510
Isn't he managing for Toni
these days?

22:17.553 --> 22:21.383
Yeah, but he's helping Archie
with some dog thing tonight,
so Toni asked me to step in.

22:21.427 --> 22:24.168
Veronica, Cheryl, Tabitha,
and I will be performing.

22:24.212 --> 22:26.170
While we keep
the truckers busy,

22:26.214 --> 22:30.174
our stealth team of Kevin
and Reggie will be
jimmying open their trailers,

22:30.218 --> 22:32.655
inspecting their trucks,
and looking for
anything suspicious.

22:32.699 --> 22:34.396
If you find something,
I'll come check it out.

22:34.440 --> 22:37.573
Our main goal of the night
is recon.

22:37.617 --> 22:41.360
Okay? Get names, get licenses,
and cardinal rule,

22:41.403 --> 22:44.841
no one goes off alone
with any truckers. Okay?

22:44.885 --> 22:46.234
Are we ready to do this?

22:50.543 --> 22:52.675
I asked around, Archie,
and it's true.

22:52.719 --> 22:54.503
The dog fighting ring in town.

22:54.547 --> 22:57.027
Once a month, sickos from
as far north as Montreal,

22:57.071 --> 22:59.508
meet at that address
to bet on dogs.

22:59.552 --> 23:01.380
That's where
the ringleader lives.

23:01.423 --> 23:02.772
When's the next round
of dogfights?

23:02.816 --> 23:04.121
Not for another
couple of weeks.

23:04.165 --> 23:06.515
Enough time to loop in
Sheriff Keller.

23:06.559 --> 23:09.823
Yeah, except we're not
looping in Sheriff Keller,
or my uncle.

23:09.866 --> 23:12.216
I don't want
this scumbag arrested.

23:12.913 --> 23:14.218
I want him hurt.

23:14.262 --> 23:16.830
Sarge, our priority
is saving the dogs.

23:16.873 --> 23:20.790
Yeah, but that doesn't mean
we can't settle up
with this guy, too.

23:20.834 --> 23:22.575
["Nothin' But A Good Time"
playing]

23:22.618 --> 23:23.663
[crowd cheering]

23:27.841 --> 23:30.626
♪ Not a dime
I can't pay my rent ♪

23:30.670 --> 23:34.456
♪ I can barely make it
through the week ♪

23:34.500 --> 23:37.851
♪ Saturday night
I wanna meet my boy ♪

23:37.894 --> 23:41.289
♪ But right now,
I couldn't make ends meet ♪

23:41.332 --> 23:45.554
♪ I'm always workin'
sweatin' every day ♪

23:45.598 --> 23:49.558
♪ Gotta get a break from that
same old, same old ♪

23:49.602 --> 23:52.518
♪ I need a chance
just to get away ♪

23:52.561 --> 23:56.347
♪ If you could hear me think
this is what I'd say ♪

23:56.391 --> 24:00.395
♪ Don't need nothin'
but a good time ♪

24:00.439 --> 24:02.919
♪ How can I resist

24:02.963 --> 24:07.228
♪ Ain't lookin' for nothin'
but a good time ♪

24:07.271 --> 24:10.797
♪ And it don't get better
than this ♪

24:10.840 --> 24:14.757
♪ They say I spend my money
on women and wine ♪

24:14.801 --> 24:18.805
♪ But I couldn't tell you
where I spent last night ♪

24:18.848 --> 24:21.851
♪ I'm really sorry about
the shape I'm in ♪

24:21.895 --> 24:25.507
♪ I just like my fun
every now and then ♪

24:25.551 --> 24:29.511
♪ I'm always workin',
sweatin' every day ♪

24:29.555 --> 24:33.384
♪ Gotta get away from
that same old, same old ♪

24:33.428 --> 24:36.126
♪ I need a chance
just to get away ♪

24:36.170 --> 24:40.304
♪ If you could hear me think
this is what I'd say ♪

24:40.348 --> 24:43.830
♪ Don't need nothin',
but a good time ♪

24:43.873 --> 24:44.961
[telephone ringing]

24:45.005 --> 24:46.833
♪ How can I resist?

24:46.876 --> 24:51.228
♪ Ain't lookin' for nothin'
but a good time ♪

24:51.272 --> 24:54.580
♪ And it don't get better
than this ♪

24:56.582 --> 25:00.499
♪ You see I raise a toast
to all of us ♪

25:00.542 --> 25:04.415
♪ Who are breakin' our backs
every day ♪

25:04.459 --> 25:08.202
♪ If wanting the good life
is such a crime ♪

25:08.245 --> 25:11.248
♪ Lord, then, put me away

25:11.292 --> 25:15.949
-♪ Don't need nothin'
but a good time ♪
-[vocalizing]

25:15.992 --> 25:18.342
♪ How can I resist?

25:18.386 --> 25:22.303
♪ Ain't lookin' for nothin'
but a good time ♪

25:22.346 --> 25:25.219
♪ And it don't get better
than this ♪

25:25.262 --> 25:27.177
[upbeat music playing
in distance]

25:28.875 --> 25:29.876
Hey, what's going on?

25:29.919 --> 25:31.442
I'm an agent with the FBI.

25:31.486 --> 25:33.227
We're investigating
illegal contraband

25:33.270 --> 25:34.794
being shipped down
from Montreal.

25:34.837 --> 25:36.970
I'm gonna need you
to open up the back.

25:37.013 --> 25:38.319
[instrumental music continues]

25:44.281 --> 25:48.285
Okay, no contraband,
but can you explain the blood?

25:48.329 --> 25:51.158
Yeah, I just did
a huge meat delivery.

25:51.201 --> 25:52.855
That's cow's blood.

25:52.899 --> 25:54.988
And I assume you have documents
and receipts to back that up.

25:55.031 --> 25:56.729
Yeah, in my cab.

25:58.469 --> 26:00.167
[music crescendos and stops]

26:02.648 --> 26:04.650
[dogs barking distantly]

26:11.744 --> 26:13.397
You guys get the dogs,
I'm going inside.

26:13.441 --> 26:14.747
Hey Sarge, hold on.

26:14.790 --> 26:16.270
Just do it.
This isn't gonna take long.

26:17.488 --> 26:19.665
[tense music playing]

26:24.713 --> 26:25.714
Those your dogs outside?

26:25.758 --> 26:26.759
Who the hell are you?

26:26.802 --> 26:28.674
I said, are those your dogs.

26:28.717 --> 26:33.461
Yeah. I train them. Why?
You wanna buy one?

26:33.504 --> 26:36.638
You and me, we're gonna
have ourselves
a real dog fight.

26:38.031 --> 26:40.163
[suspenseful music playing]

26:40.207 --> 26:42.383
[object clicking]

26:45.778 --> 26:47.562
[grunts, groans]

26:52.828 --> 26:55.396
You like that? Sicko.

26:55.439 --> 26:56.440
You like getting beaten?

26:56.484 --> 26:58.442
[Eric] Sarge, Sarge, enough.

27:01.097 --> 27:02.795
[Archie] You can call
Sheriff Keller now,
if you want.

27:02.838 --> 27:05.188
Or the garbage man,
I don't really care which.

27:05.232 --> 27:07.626
But if you touch one more dog,

27:07.669 --> 27:09.497
I'm gonna dig
your grave myself.

27:14.981 --> 27:17.940
Not a complete success,
but 57 truckers total,

27:17.984 --> 27:20.116
with their names
and driver's license numbers.

27:20.160 --> 27:23.772
Not a bad start to a list
of possible suspects, partner.

27:23.816 --> 27:26.470
Hm. I'll do some
background checks
on them tonight

27:26.514 --> 27:30.170
and tomorrow night we'll do
some more dancing and recon.

27:30.213 --> 27:31.650
No rest for the weary, huh?

27:34.130 --> 27:35.523
[doorbell chimes]

27:35.566 --> 27:37.525
[vehicle pulling over]

27:42.878 --> 27:44.880
[dramatic music plays]

27:44.924 --> 27:49.929
Hey, this is where
the Wild Foxes perform?
Saw a sign on the highway.

27:49.972 --> 27:51.974
Uh, yeah, but you missed it.

27:52.018 --> 27:54.673
Our last call was an hour ago.

27:54.716 --> 27:56.196
Come back
tomorrow night, though.

27:56.239 --> 27:58.372
Shoot. I was looking for
a good time tonight.

28:00.113 --> 28:01.505
Well, what are you doing now?

28:03.420 --> 28:05.640
[ominous music playing]

28:06.554 --> 28:09.383
Uh, I was gonna go home,

28:09.426 --> 28:15.084
but could be down
for a little fun, if you are.

28:15.128 --> 28:16.216
Yeah. Hop in.

28:16.259 --> 28:18.261
[ominous music continues]

28:22.222 --> 28:23.397
[mobile keypad clicking]

28:26.226 --> 28:27.227
[cell phone beeps]

28:27.270 --> 28:28.576
[engine starts]

28:29.403 --> 28:30.709
[cell phone beeps]

28:31.535 --> 28:33.712
[dramatic music playing]

28:35.104 --> 28:36.410
[music intensifying]

28:55.037 --> 28:55.951
[music stops]

28:59.738 --> 29:02.044
I know a motel
not too far from here.

29:02.088 --> 29:03.263
Sounds good.

29:06.440 --> 29:08.442
So, are you just
passing through town?

29:10.139 --> 29:11.750
Actually visiting
my grandmother.

29:12.446 --> 29:13.882
She's pretty sick.

29:13.926 --> 29:16.102
I'm getting ready
to say my goodbyes.

29:16.145 --> 29:17.451
I'm sorry to hear that.

29:17.494 --> 29:19.714
Oh, no. It's all right.

29:19.758 --> 29:23.892
It's a beautiful thing, really.
Watching someone pass.

29:23.936 --> 29:26.634
Watching as the light
slowly fades from their eyes.

29:28.114 --> 29:29.289
There's nothing like it.

29:32.118 --> 29:34.860
You mind if I stopped
to stretch my legs
and take a leak?

29:34.903 --> 29:36.339
No, sure.

29:36.383 --> 29:37.776
I'll be two minutes, tops.

29:37.819 --> 29:38.689
Mm.

29:55.837 --> 29:56.795
[draws knife]

29:57.621 --> 29:58.840
[ominous music plays]

30:14.769 --> 30:15.683
[yelps]

30:15.726 --> 30:16.989
[dramatic music plays]

30:20.470 --> 30:21.515
[mobile keypad clicking]

30:21.558 --> 30:23.082
[phone ringing]

30:23.125 --> 30:24.866
Tabitha, I got him.

30:24.910 --> 30:27.042
[Tabitha] I'm on my way.
Don't do anything crazy.

30:29.436 --> 30:31.655
[dramatic music plays]

30:41.535 --> 30:43.580
[motor revving]

30:43.624 --> 30:45.844
[dramatic music intensifies]

30:49.021 --> 30:49.978
[man grunts]

31:06.429 --> 31:08.431
[music crescendos]

31:09.432 --> 31:11.913
[footsteps on roof]

31:14.046 --> 31:15.482
[motor revving]

31:31.019 --> 31:32.891
[grunting]

31:37.330 --> 31:38.722
[motor roaring]

31:39.985 --> 31:40.899
[grunts]

31:43.814 --> 31:45.642
[vehicle approaching]

31:53.694 --> 31:55.914
Betty, are you okay?

31:55.957 --> 31:58.568
Yeah. I am.

31:59.613 --> 32:01.441
But I need your help with him.

32:14.106 --> 32:15.455
I'm gonna take a shower.

32:17.544 --> 32:18.501
[door closes]

32:19.633 --> 32:21.026
[Frank] Wild guess.

32:21.069 --> 32:23.158
You guys went
after the dog fighter.

32:23.202 --> 32:26.596
Yeah, Sarge went
berserk on him.

32:26.640 --> 32:28.598
I wish he wouldn't
have done that.

32:30.122 --> 32:32.428
Can't say that
I'm surprised, though.

32:32.472 --> 32:34.300
Not after what
happened to Bingo.

32:35.127 --> 32:36.693
What are you talking about?

32:37.956 --> 32:39.000
Bingo.

32:39.044 --> 32:40.393
Your platoon dog.

32:41.568 --> 32:44.136
Archie told me
how you two were...

32:44.179 --> 32:46.616
pinned down in a foxhole and...

32:47.617 --> 32:50.011
and you had to sit there
and listen to...

32:50.055 --> 32:52.622
Bingo howling and dying.

32:56.148 --> 32:57.976
Frank, Bingo wasn't a dog.

33:00.935 --> 33:02.458
He was a grunt, like me.

33:05.853 --> 33:07.115
[sighs]

33:07.159 --> 33:08.116
[shutter closing]

33:08.160 --> 33:09.813
[Tabitha] What do we do now?

33:09.857 --> 33:13.382
We find an out of the way place
to park the truck.

33:13.426 --> 33:15.558
What about the guy? The killer?

33:15.602 --> 33:18.474
I have a place where we can
take him and keep him.

33:18.518 --> 33:19.998
Shouldn't we hand him
over to the FBI?

33:20.041 --> 33:21.825
Not yet.

33:21.869 --> 33:26.004
If there is a chance
he knows where Polly is,

33:26.047 --> 33:28.745
I want him to give up
that information

33:28.789 --> 33:32.010
at which point,
we will hand him over.

33:39.539 --> 33:41.280
Arch,

33:41.323 --> 33:43.238
Eric told me
the truth about Bingo.

33:44.805 --> 33:45.806
You want to talk about it?

33:47.460 --> 33:49.070
What's there to
talk about, Uncle Frank?

33:49.114 --> 33:50.854
I've been to war, Archie.

33:50.898 --> 33:53.379
I know the impossible decisions
you have to make.

33:54.293 --> 33:55.337
To hear Eric tell it,

33:55.381 --> 33:57.383
if you had gone back for Bingo,

33:57.426 --> 33:59.602
you and Eric probably
wouldn't have made it either.

34:01.082 --> 34:02.301
You made a choice
in the moment,

34:02.344 --> 34:04.042
and it was the right choice.

34:05.913 --> 34:07.480
You can't save everyone.

34:09.351 --> 34:10.570
It feels wrong.

34:12.093 --> 34:14.269
Everything feels wrong.

34:14.313 --> 34:17.272
I'm trying to save this town,
but it is so...

34:18.143 --> 34:20.232
corrupt...

34:20.275 --> 34:23.322
broken, full of awful,
despicable people.

34:23.365 --> 34:25.585
I mean, the lowest
of the lows, dog fighters.

34:27.282 --> 34:30.372
Makes me think there's
nothing worth saving here.

34:30.416 --> 34:32.461
Don't lose sight of
what you're doing, Archie.

34:38.293 --> 34:39.816
[Cheryl] Kevin,

34:39.860 --> 34:41.862
I heard you being summoned
to Weatherbee's office.

34:41.905 --> 34:44.386
Were you fired on account of
your cruising ways?

34:44.430 --> 34:47.433
No, Cheryl, actually,
the opposite.

34:47.476 --> 34:49.783
I've just been named
Teacher of the Year.

34:49.826 --> 34:52.002
Oh, but that's incredible.

34:52.046 --> 34:54.222
So why the forlorn face?

34:55.049 --> 34:56.050
Is it Fangs?

34:56.094 --> 34:57.443
Yeah.

34:57.486 --> 34:59.836
But also it's my entire life.

34:59.880 --> 35:04.102
Like, I love being a teacher,
but it was never supposed
to be my life's calling.

35:05.451 --> 35:07.496
This award is
a painful reminder

35:07.540 --> 35:09.977
of all that I haven't
accomplished, okay?

35:10.020 --> 35:14.416
I'm supposed to be in New York
writing, performing, directing.

35:14.460 --> 35:17.680
Instead, I'm in Riverdale,
still cruising the woods.

35:18.725 --> 35:20.466
Unlucky in love.

35:20.509 --> 35:22.772
Being named
Teacher of the Year
at a dying high school, okay?

35:22.816 --> 35:25.253
This can't be my life.
It just it... it can't be.

35:25.297 --> 35:29.301
I think I have an idea
that might not fix
all of your problems,

35:29.344 --> 35:32.652
but will replenish
your artist's soul.

35:34.915 --> 35:36.917
[dogs barking]

35:38.005 --> 35:40.312
Well, what do you think?

35:40.355 --> 35:42.618
Not everybody in Riverdale
is rotten, Archie.

35:43.880 --> 35:45.491
Uncle Frank, how did
you guys pull this off?

35:45.534 --> 35:47.188
Eric and I called
a couple shelters.

35:47.232 --> 35:48.885
We told 'em
we had a bunch of dogs
that needed homes.

35:48.929 --> 35:50.191
Good dogs

35:50.235 --> 35:51.845
who maybe need a little more

35:51.888 --> 35:54.282
attention and rehabilitation
before they can get adopted...

35:54.326 --> 35:56.197
because of what
they've been through.

35:56.241 --> 35:58.025
Almost gives you
hope again, huh?

35:58.068 --> 35:59.157
Almost.

36:01.028 --> 36:03.204
No, this is good.
This is great.

36:03.248 --> 36:06.773
Hey, Sarge,
you think it'd be okay
if we call him Bingo?

36:06.816 --> 36:08.862
Wouldn't be disrespectful.
Would it?

36:08.905 --> 36:10.342
No, no. Hey!

36:11.386 --> 36:12.605
We love Bingo.

36:13.823 --> 36:14.955
I think he'd be honored.

36:23.355 --> 36:24.834
Brothers and sisters,

36:24.878 --> 36:29.883
this week, I learned
a simple yet profound truth.

36:31.145 --> 36:33.452
It is in making those around us

36:33.495 --> 36:36.759
feel good that we ourselves
may find salvation,

36:37.195 --> 36:38.326
comfort.

36:38.370 --> 36:41.111
[Cheryl] Yes, comfort,
my people.

36:41.155 --> 36:43.244
Isaiah, chapter 40, verse one.

36:43.288 --> 36:46.465
As a reminder of that lesson,
today's closing hymn will be

36:46.508 --> 36:51.644
Everything is Alright
from the iconic musical
Jesus Christ Superstar

36:51.687 --> 36:53.689
and singing with me
will be our ministry's

36:53.733 --> 36:56.126
new artistic director
Kevin Keller.

36:56.170 --> 36:58.346
[people clapping]

37:02.829 --> 37:05.048
♪ Try not to get worried ♪

37:05.092 --> 37:10.619
♪ Try not to turn on to
Problems that upset you, oh ♪

37:10.663 --> 37:13.709
♪ Don't you know
everything's all right ♪

37:13.753 --> 37:15.885
♪ Yes, everything's fine ♪

37:15.929 --> 37:20.542
♪ And we want you
To sleep well tonight ♪

37:20.586 --> 37:24.546
♪ Let the world turn
Without you tonight ♪

37:24.590 --> 37:27.549
♪ If we try we'll get by ♪

37:27.593 --> 37:30.073
♪ So forget
All about us tonight ♪

37:30.117 --> 37:34.687
♪ Everything's all right, yes
Everything's all right, yes ♪

